<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2010/07/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>saltminion</id>
    <title>Salt Minion</title>
    <version>3000.0.0</version>
    <authors>SaltStack</authors>
    <owners>Derek Murawsky, Alex Clay, espoelstra, Arthur REGNARD</owners>
    <summary>Salt Minion Installer</summary>
    <description>
        This package installs a Salt-Minion on your system as a Windows service. The Salt-Minion receives commands from the central Salt-Master and replies with the results of said commands. It can also be used in standalone mode to apply states to a machine without a Salt-Master by using `C:\salt\salt-call.bat --local state.sls [yoursls]` or similar commands with `--local`.

        Note that this package supports arguments:
            - `/master=[master_name]`: A string value to set the IP address or hostname of the Salt-Master. Default value is 'salt'.
            - `/minion=[minion_name]`: A string value to set the Salt-Minion name. Default value is hostname. (note: the installer itself uses `/minion-name`, but parsing dictionary keys with the `-` is painful).
            - `/norunning`: If present, did not start the Salt-Minion after installation. (note: new param in version 3000.0.0)
        These arguments can be passed to the package via the `--params '/master=myMaster /minion=myMinion /norunning'`.
    </description>
